#
#  link_rules
#

The following command shows how to link a Fortran90 application with the ESMF 
shared libraries on Linux. In the command, the Fortran90 application is 
called "myModel".

It is assumed that the ESMF libraries have been built successfully at ESMF_DIR 
with the following environment variables:
ESMF_OS = Linux
ESMF_COMPILER = pgi
ESMF_ABI = 32
ESMF_SITE = longs
ESMF_COMM = mpiuni
ESMF_BOPT = g or O

To simplify the link rules, first define MODDIR and LIBDIR.

MODDIR = ${ESMF_DIR}/mod/mod${ESMF_BOPT}/Linux.pgi.32.default
LIBDIR = ${ESMF_DIR}/lib/lib${ESMF_BOPT}/Linux.pgi.32.default

Also define:
LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/local/pgi/linux86/lib

The link rules are:

pgf90 -I${MODDIR} -o myModel myModel.F -L${LIBDIR} -lesmf -lmpiuni -lpgc -lstd -lC


